     8	## One-page summary
     9	
    10	The single-world engine is the measured donor arena, called **K0**. The
    11	non-React entry point is a DIRECT build whose emitted hot paths are the donor
    12	hot paths: no receipt checks, fork calls, or world branches. Importing the
    13	React binding activates the LOGGED build monotonically. Every later write,
    14	urgent or deferred, appends a receipt before it updates K0. Receipts are
    15	replayed in write order, filtered by a render pass's token set, sequence pin,
    16	and immutable per-root committed-prefix view. This is React's update-queue
    17	arithmetic expressed for a many-consumer store.
    18	
    19	The consolidation rule is deliberately coarse: **if any unswept receipt
    20	exists anywhere, every render-phase signal read uses its exact pinned world**.
    21	The same is true after that pass stages a hook evaluator. Only a render pass
    22	with no receipt history and no staged evaluator may read K0 directly. Core
    23	reads outside React still read K0's newest state. This rule deletes the
    24	`WORLD_TAINT` bit, its missing tracked-serve propagation, per-node staged
    25	probes, `RENDER_NEWEST` and its demotions, and the saturation spill flag. A
    26	receipt cannot disappear while an older pass needs it: retirement may release
    27	the receipt's 5-bit slot, but compaction of the receipt itself waits until all
    28	live pins include its retirement. Therefore the coarse gate remains closed
    29	for every pass that could otherwise see a cache from the wrong world.
    30	
    31	World evaluations record real dependency edges in a second, add-only arena,
    32	**K1**. K0 remains unchanged. Every write performs a value-blind reach walk
    33	over K0 union K1 and calls each reached watcher's `setState` synchronously in
    34	the writer's batch context. A per-walk generation terminates union cycles;
    35	full walks execute no user code and edge-add deliveries use the already
    36	required deferred-delivery drain, so walks never nest and one `lastWalk`
    37	column is sufficient. K1 also preserves K0 edges removed while receipt
    38	history exists. At quiescence, observed K1 nodes refresh into K0 and K1 resets;
    39	a twice-writing refresh target carries its full reverse-reachable K1 cone.
