   828	## 11. Lifecycles, counters, and reclamation
   829	
   830	| item | minted/set | retained by | clear/reset and collision defense |
   831	|---|---|---|---|
   832	| `globalSeq` | writes, retirements, views, stages | receipts, pins, stamps, ids | quiescent renumber rewrites retained values and bumps episode |
   833	| token serial | F1 | fork registry, receipts | never reused live; wrap only after quiescence + token epoch bump |
   834	| slot + `slotGen` | live-token claim | live token, masks, receipts | reach state clears at retirement; gen increments before reuse |
   835	| `wc[slot,gen]` | each write | basis headers | zeroed only after gen increments; gen mismatch invalidates |
   836	| pass pin/id | F2 start | pass, memo pins | pass end; ids generation-checked |
   837	| `lockViewId` | every view re-mint | root, pass, basis | pooled view dies after refs; episode in every key |
   838	| lineage id | F5 | stage records, capsules | lineage death; fork generation prevents reuse collision |
   839	| `stageId` | changed lineage deps | records, basis, F9 | globalSeq/episode; unpublished records swept |
   840	| `walkGen/lastWalk` | each full walk | K0/K1 records | with `walkDepth=0`, wrap clears the whole column then restarts at 1 |
   841	| node/link gen | allocator reuse | edges, memos, watchers | increment before free-list reuse; mismatch rejects |
   842	| `retireVisStamp` | retirement touching atom | bases, snapshots | globalSeq/episode renumber |
   843	| capsule generation | content change | thenable callbacks | increment before suffix reuse; stale settlements ignored |
   844	| receipt count | append/sweep | render gate, E-PRESERVE | reaches zero only after all tapes empty |
   845	
   846	Quiescent global renumber runs only at an operation boundary with no active
   847	walk. Forced-small-counter tests invoke the same rewrite. If a configured
   848	horizon is reached with live passes/tokens, the runtime performs a full
   849	order-preserving rewrite under the existing operation-boundary stop; it does
   850	not wrap. `walkGen` has its own whole-column clear because full walks cannot
   851	nest.
   852	
   853	Abandoned fresh arena nodes are reclaimed through pass-owned allocation
   854	lists: commit transfers them to ordinary ownership; discard returns their
   855	records after generation increment. StrictMode repeated mount/abandon cannot
   856	grow the bump plane without bound.
   857	
   858	## 12. Tracing and diagnostics
   859	
   860	Tracing is a lazily imported module. Each event site performs one recorder-
   861	slot check. When absent it allocates nothing. Ring mode writes fixed integer
   862	records into a preallocated plane and overwrites old records with a loss
   863	counter; lossless-session mode grows only at operation boundaries. Events
   864	include write/token/seq, pass and world ids, fold decisions, K0/K1 edges,
   865	delivery cause, F9 publication, lock view, retirement, carrier fallback, and
   866	effect flush.
   867	
   868	Queries walk integer causality links for “why did this watcher render?”, “why
   869	is this memo invalid?”, and “which receipt is visible here?”. Graphviz exports
   870	K0, K1, and a selected world without mutating them. Labels are cold side data.
   871	
   872	Development assertions include the strong E-PRESERVE reach comparison, mask
   873	generation checks, pass/lock ordering, publication ownership, reducer-fold
   874	guard, no-user-code full walks, and receipt-count/tape agreement.
   875	
