   945	### A2 — `walkGen` under edge-add delivery reentrancy
   946	
   947	Setup: K0 union K1 contains `c->d->c`; an outer write walk reaches a place
   948	where React work later creates an edge carrying another live token.
   949	
   950	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
   951	|---|---|---|
   952	| 1 | outer delivery walk | set `walkDepth=1`, mint G1; stamp c then d; d's edge to c sees G1 and stops |
   953	| 2 | watcher enqueue | `setState` only appends React work; it invokes no render or user callback inside the walk |
   954	| 3 | edge-add request while depth 1 | existing deferred edge-delivery drain records `(token,edge,slotGen)`; it does not start a full walk or overwrite `lastWalk` |
   955	| 4 | outer completion | set depth 0; every G1 record was visited once |
   956	| 5 | drain | generation/liveness-check the queued token; invoke `runInBatch`; any required new full walk now mints G2 after G1 is finished |
   957	| 6 | reducer/effect variants | reducer/equality/evaluation happened before the walk under guards; effects flush after the drain, so none can nest a full walk |
   958	
   959	outcome: a single `lastWalk` cell is sufficient because full walks are
   960	serialized with the already existing edge-delivery drain.
