   987	### A4 — lineage-stable ids under deps oscillation and lineage changes
   988	
   989	Setup: one hook sees deps A, then B, then A across retries of lineage L; a
   990	second lineage L2 later renders the hook.
   991	
   992	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
   993	|---|---|---|
   994	| 1 | L/A | A equals committed record E0; reuse E0 stage id, no unpublished stage |
   995	| 2 | L/B | mint E1 with `stageId=publicationId=s1`; store as L's current record |
   996	| 3 | pure B retry | deps equal E1; reuse s1, so the positional capsule identity/basis does not churn |
   997	| 4 | L/A | compare committed first; reuse E0. If A were only an older unpublished alternative, mint E2; common-basis value revalidation retains resources whose input stayed equal |
   998	| 5 | L abandonment / lineage death | E1/E2 publish nothing and die when unreferenced; an ordinary retry discard retains the lineage pointer |
   999	| 6 | L2 | cannot reuse unpublished L records; it selects committed E0 or mints its own record |
  1000	| 7 | L commit-B variant | F9 promotes E1; L2 may now select E1 as the immutable committed record |
  1001	
  1002	outcome: pure retries are stable, oscillation has React/useMemo semantics,
  1003	and unpublished identities cannot leak across lineages.
  1004	
  1005	residual risk: deps comparison and record retention are pinned by A/B/A,
  1006	StrictMode, discard, and forced-id-wrap rows.
  1007	
  1008	### A5 — value-revalidated prefixes through staged evaluators
  1009	
  1010	Setup: a staged child evaluator changes stage id before a downstream
  1011	`ctx.use(factory)`. In one branch the child's equality-stable output is the
  1012	same; in the other it changes. The prefix depth is N.
  1013	
  1014	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
  1015	|---|---|---|
  1016	| 1 | retry basis compare | child `(id,oldStage,oldValueRef)` mismatches current stage id |
