  1387	### C14: StrictMode and replay
  1388	
  1389	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
  1390	|---|---|---|
  1391	| 1 | double render | reads only create pass-owned memos/K1 additions/stages; K1 additions are idempotent; no render write is allowed |
  1392	| 2 | first attempt discarded | memo pins, fresh nodes, and F9 attachments release by generation; F9 emits nothing; lineage stage/capsule records remain for a same-lineage replay |
  1393	| 3 | replay with equal deps | lineage record and stage id reuse; same positional capsule/thenable returned |
  1394	| 4 | replay with changed deps | new stage id; common basis forces recompute/value validation before capsule reuse |
  1395	| 5 | double mount/unmount | refcounts flap but microtask damping starts one observed effect and cleans after stable zero |
  1396	| 6 | throwing/suspending getter | sentinel box closes tracking in `finally`; graph contains only completed edges |
  1397	
  1398	outcome: replay is pure, resources retain stable identity, and lifecycle
  1399	effects net correctly.
  1400	
  1401	residual risk: Offscreen/StrictMode ordering changes; fork F9 tests and the
  1402	React harness run in dev and production builds.
  1403	
  1404	### C15: Suspense across worlds and batch sets
  1405	
  1406	Setup: k makes c suspend; a component mounts in k; later the promise settles.
  1407	
  1408	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
  1409	|---|---|---|
  1410	| 1 | k write/pass | receipt count forces exact world; c evaluates with k atoms and reaches `ctx.use(factory)` |
  1411	| 2 | capsule create | key `(cGen,lineageL,position)`; store thenable q and common basis prefix for full k world; React `use` suspends on q |
  1412	| 3 | committed/excluding render | exact-evaluates its own world and cannot see L's q or suspension; a non-React core NEWEST getter follows its separately documented newest contract |
  1413	| 4 | mount mid-transition | same lineage/world reaches same position; equal basis returns q and suspends on first render |
  1414	| 5 | q settles | settlement version dirties the k memo and schedules retry; q identity remains |
  1415	| 6 | retry | lineage L stable; basis values equal -> consume q's settled value, no refetch |
  1416	| 7 | multi-batch `{k,j}` | F5 gives the joint logical lineage; basis header/mask/clocks distinguish it from k-only without using one token as identity |
  1417	| 8 | included write changed input | clock/fingerprint moves; re-fold differs -> drop suffix/refetch once |
  1418	| 9 | lock/retire/evaluator id moved but input equal | value revalidation retains old reference, restamps basis, and reuses q |
  1419	| 10 | commit | root lock contains rendered prefixes; lineage dies after committed consumers transfer; stale settlements check capsule gen |
  1420	
  1421	outcome: thenable identity survives pure retries, while actual world content
  1422	changes invalidate it.
  1423	
  1424	residual risk: deep flattened basis cost and factory purity; typeahead/deep-
  1425	prefix gate and lazy-factory tests pin both.
  1426	
  1427	### C16: effects observe committed state only
  1428	
  1429	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
  1430	|---|---|---|
  1431	| 1 | default D writes a | K0 NEWEST becomes new; D receipt live; write queue may note effect E but E's committed snapshot is unchanged |
  1432	| 2 | unrelated token retires/flushes | `useSignalEffect` evaluates committed-for-root world whose LV excludes D; exact fold returns old a; basis value equal, so no new-value observation |
  1433	| 3 | core effect variant | documented NEWEST contract may read K0 new immediately; separate API, expected |
  1434	| 4 | D root commit | LV locks D prefix before effects; D's durable TL forces E revalidation; it now reads new a and runs |
  1435	| 5 | D store-only retirement | retirement stamp/TL similarly exposes and flushes committed value even without React work |
  1436	| 6 | effect deps change | React native effect re-fire cleans, runs new function, records new K0/K1 dependencies; no F9 staging path |
  1437	
  1438	outcome: React effects never observe applied-but-uncommitted D, then observe it
  1439	at the commit/retirement edge that makes it committed.
  1440	
  1441	residual risk: a fast queue bypassing durable trigger enumeration; tests
  1442	consume the queue early and require the later TL drain to fire.
  1443	
  1444	### C17: optimistic rollback
  1445	
  1446	| step | actor/mechanism | state touched (values, marks, edges, log, lanes) |
  1447	|---|---|---|
  1448	| 1 | API inspection | no truncate/rollback method is exported from Atom, transition helpers, fork protocol, or ActionScope |
  1449	| 2 | React abandonment | `committed=false` retirement still folds receipts; it is not rollback |
  1450	| 3 | attempted internal call | no policy entry point exists; TypeScript and compiled-export snapshots reject it |
  1451	
