     1	# Requirements (frozen seed)
     2	
     3	What the product is: a from-scratch TypeScript signals library with
     4	no-compromise concurrent React integration (no `useSyncExternalStore`), backed
     5	by a React fork we fully control. These requirements are the contract; the
     6	architecture is the design space.
     7	
     8	## R — Functional (the user-facing chrome; largely settled by prior work)
     9	
    10	- **R1 Atom**: `new Atom<T>({ state, effect?, isEqual?, label? })`;
    11	  `atom.state` (tracked read), `set(v)`, `update(fn)`. `effect` runs on
    12	  observed 0→1 with cleanup on 1→0, microtask-debounced (flap-proof).
    13	- **R2 Computed**: `new Computed<T>({ fn(ctx), isEqual?, label? })`; lazy,
    14	  cached, exact re-verification; `ctx.use(thenable)` suspense with per-world
    15	  positional identity; `ctx.previous`. Errors/suspensions are cached values
    16	  (sentinel boxes) — a throwing getter can never corrupt graph state.
    17	- **R3 ReducerAtom**: `dispatch(action)`; actions are logged and replayed per
    18	  world; parity with `useReducer` is a conformance test, not a hope.
    19	- **R4 Hooks** (`cosignal/react`): `useSignal`, `useAtom`, `useReducerAtom`,
    20	  `useComputed(fn, deps, opts?)` (closes over props/state; signal reads
    21	  auto-tracked), `useSignalEffect(fn, deps?)` (committed state only).
    22	  Provider-free preferred; a provider component is acceptable if it
    23	  demonstrably buys correctness or simplicity (justify the trade).
    24	- **R5 Transitions**: full `startTransition`/`useTransition` parity — signal
    25	  and React state move in lockstep; optional `startSignalTransition` /
    26	  `useSignalTransition` throughput helpers.
    27	- **R6 Suspense parity**, including the mount-mid-transition-while-suspending
    28	  case (react-concurrent-store's documented known bug must be a passing test),
    29	  and fresh nodes (`useComputed` mounted mid-transition) reading the pass's
    30	  world correctly on first render.
    31	- **R7 Infinite-loop rejection**: React's own limits for React-coupled storms;
    32	  engine cycle detection for signal-only loops.
    33	- **R8 Writes inside computeds**: tolerated when acyclic;
    34	  `configure({forbidWritesInComputeds})`; render-world evaluation always
    35	  rejects writes.
    36	- **R9 Multiple roots**: per-root self-consistency is required (a root must
    37	  never contradict its own committed DOM). Cross-root simultaneity for a
    38	  spanning batch is NOT required; the design declares its multi-root scope
    39	  and walks C11 at that declared scope (full / degraded / v1 single-root
    40	  with loud detection).
    41	- **R10 SSR/hydration** from serialized atom state (RSC/Flight out of scope v1).
    42	- **R11 Tracing**: lazily-loadable, zero-allocation recorder (ring + lossless
    43	  session modes), causality queries, Graphviz renderers; untraced cost = one
    44	  slot check per site. (The synthesized spec §16 is the reference bar; reuse
    45	  it unless the architecture forces changes.)
    46	- **R12 React fork**: see `fork-charter.md` — the old "minimal additive patch"
    47	  constraint is lifted; maintainability is a scored axis instead.
    48	- **R13 Core non-React API**: `effect()`, `batch()`, `untracked()`,
    49	  `configure()` (`effectScope()` optional — include only if it earns its
    50	  keep). Scheduling/flush behavior may be configurable; the hard requirement
    51	  is **benchmark integrability**: the design must drive the
    52	  js-reactivity-benchmark adapter honestly (exact pull counts, checksum
    53	  contracts, fresh mid-batch reads, effects observable synchronously under
    54	  some documented configuration).
    55	
    56	## P — Performance (gates, not adjectives)
    57	
    58	- **P1** Signal-driven re-render within 10% of equivalent `useState`;
    59	  10k-subscription mount within 15%.
    60	- **P2** Pure-core (no React) at-or-below alien-signals v3 on every tier-0
    61	  shape; exact pull counts (`testPullCounts: true`); 179/179 conformance
    62	  including growth stress. Donor reference points in `research-facts.md`.
    63	- **P3** Concurrency machinery costs ~nothing when inactive: pure-core users
    64	  execute zero concurrency instructions; React-mounted-but-quiet ≤2% on
    65	  tier-0; every hot mechanism carries a numeric gate and a CI check (the
    66	  synthesized spec's §18 gate-table style is the bar).
    67	- **P4** Zero engine allocation on steady re-render traffic; memory wins
    68	  reported as heapUsed + plane bytes side by side.
    69	
    70	## E — Engineering
    71	
    72	- pnpm workspaces; TypeScript; `type` over `interface`; `undefined` over
    73	  `null` (each `null` justified); ships compiled JS (same-file `const enum`
    74	  allowed per the measured bundler-demotion hazard); branded id types;
    75	  `__DEV__` by define, never by runtime const.
    76	- Process apparatus is inherited, not redesigned: oracle-first sequencing,
    77	  frozen-kernel contract suite, bytecode budgets CI, pre-registered
    78	  experiments, per-milestone numeric exit gates. (These survived review;
    79	  spend design tokens elsewhere.)
    80	- Plain-spoken spec: every concept defined in plain English before use; the
    81	  concurrency story must fit on one page (judged).
    82	
    83	## Non-negotiable correctness bar
    84	
    85	Every case in `correctness-cases.md`, walked mechanism-by-mechanism.
    86	`useState`/`useReducer`/`startTransition` parity is the product.

